{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014M7Y2j5zb3K55mipQwFb4x","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: \"PRD-224.6\"\n3\ttitle: \"commit_transcript BuiltIn + transcripts layout\"\n4\tkind: task\n5\tstatus: ready\n6\tpriority: high\n7\teffort: s\n8\tcapability: moderate\n9\tparent: \"[[PRD-224-harness-invariants-honest-state]]\"\n10\tdepends_on: []\n11\tblocks: []\n12\timpacts:\n13\t  - src/darkfactory/builtins.py\n14\t  - src/darkfactory/runner.py\n15\t  - src/darkfactory/workflow.py\n16\t  - .gitattributes\n17\t  - tests/test_builtins.py\n18\tworkflow: null\n19\ttarget_version: null\n20\tcreated: 2026-04-08\n21\tupdated: 2026-04-08\n22\ttags:\n23\t  - harness\n24\t  - invariants\n25\t  - hygiene\n26\t---\n27\t\n28\t# commit_transcript BuiltIn + transcripts layout\n29\t\n30\t## Summary\n31\t\n32\tA new `commit_transcript` BuiltIn that moves the agent transcript from the temporary location to `.darkfactory/transcripts/PRD-X-{ISO8601}.log`, stages it, and ensures the next `commit` BuiltIn picks it up. One file per agent invocation, timestamped, never overwritten.\n33\t\n34\tThis is a `[primitive]` — composable into any workflow's task list.\n35\t\n36\t## Requirements\n37\t\n38\t1. Create a `commit_transcript` BuiltIn that:\n39\t   - Reads the transcript from the temporary location written by `runner.py` (currently `.harness-agent-output.log` or similar).\n40\t   - Moves it to `.darkfactory/transcripts/PRD-X-{ISO8601}.log` where ISO8601 is the invocation timestamp.\n41\t   - Stages the file with `git add`.\n42\t   - One file per agent invocation — never overwrite existing transcripts.\n43\t2. Update the default workflow to insert `commit_transcript` before the final `commit` step.\n44\t3. Ensure `.darkfactory/transcripts/` is NOT in `.gitignore`.\n45\t4. Add `.gitattributes` entry marking `*.log` under `.darkfactory/transcripts/` as `linguist-generated=true` so GitHub collapses them in PR diffs.\n46\t5. If no transcript exists (e.g. dry-run or the runner didn't produce one), the BuiltIn is a no-op.\n47\t6. Custom workflows can omit `commit_transcript` if they don't want transcript persistence.\n48\t\n49\t## Technical Approach\n50\t\n51\t### `src/darkfactory/builtins.py`\n52\t\n53\t```python\n54\tdef commit_transcript(ctx: ExecutionContext) -> None:\n55\t    \"\"\"Move agent transcript to .darkfactory/transcripts/ and stage it.\"\"\"\n56\t    src = ctx.worktree_root / \".harness-agent-output.log\"\n57\t    if not src.exists():\n58\t        logger.info(\"No transcript found; skipping\")\n59\t        return\n60\t\n61\t    transcript_dir = ctx.worktree_root / \".darkfactory\" / \"transcripts\"\n62\t    transcript_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n63\t\n64\t    timestamp = ctx.invocation_timestamp.strftime(\"%Y-%m-%dT%H-%M-%S\")\n65\t    dest = transcript_dir / f\"{ctx.prd_id}-{timestamp}.log\"\n66\t\n67\t    shutil.move(str(src), str(dest))\n68\t\n69\t    subprocess.run([\"git\", \"add\", str(dest)], cwd=ctx.worktree_root, check=True)\n70\t    logger.info(f\"Transcript staged: {dest.relative_to(ctx.worktree_root)}\")\n71\t```\n72\t\n73\t### `src/darkfactory/runner.py`\n74\t\n75\tEnsure the transcript is written to a known location that `commit_transcript` can find. If the transcript path needs adjustment, update it here.\n76\t\n77\t### `.gitattributes`\n78\t\n79\t```\n80\t.darkfactory/transcripts/*.log linguist-generated=true\n81\t```\n82\t\n83\t### Default workflow\n84\t\n85\tInsert `commit_transcript` in the task list before the final `commit` step.\n86\t\n87\t### Tests\n88\t\n89\t- Test `commit_transcript` with a mock transcript file -> verify it's moved and staged.\n90\t- Test `commit_transcript` with no transcript file -> verify no-op.\n91\t- Test that multiple invocations produce separate timestamped files.\n92\t\n93\t## Acceptance Criteria\n94\t\n95\t- [ ] AC-1: `commit_transcript` BuiltIn exists and is registered.\n96\t- [ ] AC-2: An agent invocation creates a file at `.darkfactory/transcripts/PRD-X-{timestamp}.log`.\n97\t- [ ] AC-3: The transcript file is staged by `commit_transcript` and committed by the subsequent `commit` step.\n98\t- [ ] AC-4: `.gitattributes` marks transcript logs as `linguist-generated=true`.\n99\t- [ ] AC-5: If no transcript exists, `commit_transcript` is a no-op (no error).\n100\t- [ ] AC-6: Multiple invocations produce separate files, never overwriting.\n101\t- [ ] AC-7: Unit tests pass for all described scenarios.\n102\t\n103\t## Notes\n104\t\n105\t- Bloat: ~100KB per transcript x ~100 PRDs/year = ~10MB/year. Acceptable for now.\n106\t- Security: transcripts may contain file contents. A future `prd validate --check-transcripts` can scan for token-shaped strings.\n107\t- Layout assumes `.darkfactory/` discovery (PRD-222.1). Until then, use `<repo_root>/.darkfactory/transcripts/` directly.\n108\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"486cefb7-8454-4ea9-8512-7a451e5c819b","uuid":"ed751fce-e54e-421c-a76a-e386845bbbf0","timestamp":"2026-04-08T16:23:13.627Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/prds/PRD-224.6-commit-transcript.md","content":"---\nid: \"PRD-224.6\"\ntitle: \"commit_transcript BuiltIn + transcripts layout\"\nkind: task\nstatus: ready\npriority: high\neffort: s\ncapability: moderate\nparent: \"[[PRD-224-harness-invariants-honest-state]]\"\ndepends_on: []\nblocks: []\nimpacts:\n  - src/darkfactory/builtins.py\n  - src/darkfactory/runner.py\n  - src/darkfactory/workflow.py\n  - .gitattributes\n  - tests/test_builtins.py\nworkflow: null\ntarget_version: null\ncreated: 2026-04-08\nupdated: 2026-04-08\ntags:\n  - harness\n  - invariants\n  - hygiene\n---\n\n# commit_transcript BuiltIn + transcripts layout\n\n## Summary\n\nA new `commit_transcript` BuiltIn that moves the agent transcript from the temporary location to `.darkfactory/transcripts/PRD-X-{ISO8601}.log`, stages it, and ensures the next `commit` BuiltIn picks it up. One file per agent invocation, timestamped, never overwritten.\n\nThis is a `[primitive]` — composable into any workflow's task list.\n\n## Requirements\n\n1. Create a `commit_transcript` BuiltIn that:\n   - Reads the transcript from the temporary location written by `runner.py` (currently `.harness-agent-output.log` or similar).\n   - Moves it to `.darkfactory/transcripts/PRD-X-{ISO8601}.log` where ISO8601 is the invocation timestamp.\n   - Stages the file with `git add`.\n   - One file per agent invocation — never overwrite existing transcripts.\n2. Update the default workflow to insert `commit_transcript` before the final `commit` step.\n3. Ensure `.darkfactory/transcripts/` is NOT in `.gitignore`.\n4. Add `.gitattributes` entry marking `*.log` under `.darkfactory/transcripts/` as `linguist-generated=true` so GitHub collapses them in PR diffs.\n5. If no transcript exists (e.g. dry-run or the runner didn't produce one), the BuiltIn is a no-op.\n6. Custom workflows can omit `commit_transcript` if they don't want transcript persistence.\n\n## Technical Approach\n\n### `src/darkfactory/builtins.py`\n\n```python\ndef commit_transcript(ctx: ExecutionContext) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Move agent transcript to .darkfactory/transcripts/ and stage it.\"\"\"\n    src = ctx.worktree_root / \".harness-agent-output.log\"\n    if not src.exists():\n        logger.info(\"No transcript found; skipping\")\n        return\n\n    transcript_dir = ctx.worktree_root / \".darkfactory\" / \"transcripts\"\n    transcript_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n    timestamp = ctx.invocation_timestamp.strftime(\"%Y-%m-%dT%H-%M-%S\")\n    dest = transcript_dir / f\"{ctx.prd_id}-{timestamp}.log\"\n\n    shutil.move(str(src), str(dest))\n\n    subprocess.run([\"git\", \"add\", str(dest)], cwd=ctx.worktree_root, check=True)\n    logger.info(f\"Transcript staged: {dest.relative_to(ctx.worktree_root)}\")\n```\n\n### `src/darkfactory/runner.py`\n\nEnsure the transcript is written to a known location that `commit_transcript` can find. If the transcript path needs adjustment, update it here.\n\n### `.gitattributes`\n\n```\n.darkfactory/transcripts/*.log linguist-generated=true\n```\n\n### Default workflow\n\nInsert `commit_transcript` in the task list before the final `commit` step.\n\n### Tests\n\n- Test `commit_transcript` with a mock transcript file -> verify it's moved and staged.\n- Test `commit_transcript` with no transcript file -> verify no-op.\n- Test that multiple invocations produce separate timestamped files.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC-1: `commit_transcript` BuiltIn exists and is registered.\n- [ ] AC-2: An agent invocation creates a file at `.darkfactory/transcripts/PRD-X-{timestamp}.log`.\n- [ ] AC-3: The transcript file is staged by `commit_transcript` and committed by the subsequent `commit` step.\n- [ ] AC-4: `.gitattributes` marks transcript logs as `linguist-generated=true`.\n- [ ] AC-5: If no transcript exists, `commit_transcript` is a no-op (no error).\n- [ ] AC-6: Multiple invocations produce separate files, never overwriting.\n- [ ] AC-7: Unit tests pass for all described scenarios.\n\n## Notes\n\n- Bloat: ~100KB per transcript x ~100 PRDs/year = ~10MB/year. Acceptable for now.\n- Security: transcripts may contain file contents. A future `prd validate --check-transcripts` can scan for token-shaped strings.\n- Layout assumes `.darkfactory/` discovery (PRD-222.1). Until then, use `<repo_root>/.darkfactory/transcripts/` directly.\n","numLines":108,"startLine":1,"totalLines":108}}}
