{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HiCZTNJ4tSNnLHEbr6PAj9","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"Workflow execution engine — walks a workflow's tasks against a context.\n2\t\n3\tThe runner is the glue between every other module in the harness:\n4\t\n5\t- It holds an :class:`~darkfactory.workflow.ExecutionContext` and\n6\t  threads it through the task list.\n7\t- For each :class:`~darkfactory.workflow.BuiltIn`, it looks up the\n8\t  named function in :data:`~darkfactory.builtins.BUILTINS` and calls\n9\t  it with the context + formatted kwargs.\n10\t- For each :class:`~darkfactory.workflow.AgentTask`, it composes the\n11\t  prompt via :func:`~darkfactory.templates.compose_prompt`, picks the\n12\t  model (explicit override > capability mapping > sonnet fallback),\n13\t  invokes Claude Code via :func:`~darkfactory.invoke.invoke_claude`,\n14\t  and stores the output on the context.\n15\t- For each :class:`~darkfactory.workflow.ShellTask`, it runs the\n16\t  formatted command and handles the configured ``on_failure`` policy.\n17\t\n18\tThe runner does **not** know how to create branches, manage\n19\tworktrees, or open PRs — those are built-in tasks. Its only job is\n20\tthe dispatch loop and the retry-on-failure bookkeeping.\n21\t\n22\tRetry semantics: when a ShellTask fails with\n23\t``on_failure=\"retry_agent\"``, the runner looks backward in the task\n24\tlist for the most recent AgentTask, re-invokes it with the failed\n25\toutput bound to ``{{CHECK_OUTPUT}}``, and re-runs the failed shell\n26\ttask once. If it still fails, the runner gives up and marks the\n27\tPRD blocked (via a separate ``set_status`` built-in call).\n28\t\n29\tDry-run mode: when ``ctx.dry_run=True``, every built-in and shell\n30\ttask logs what it would do without executing. Agent tasks return a\n31\tsynthetic success result via :func:`~darkfactory.invoke.invoke_claude`'s\n32\t``dry_run=True`` path. This is what ``prd plan`` uses.\n33\t\"\"\"\n34\t\n35\tfrom __future__ import annotations\n36\t\n37\timport logging\n38\timport subprocess\n39\tfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\n40\tfrom pathlib import Path\n41\tfrom typing import TYPE_CHECKING\n42\t\n43\tfrom .builtins import BUILTINS\n44\tfrom .invoke import InvokeResult, capability_to_model, invoke_claude\n45\tfrom .templates import compose_prompt\n46\tfrom .workflow import (\n47\t    AgentTask,\n48\t    BuiltIn,\n49\t    ExecutionContext,\n50\t    ShellTask,\n51\t    Task,\n52\t    Workflow,\n53\t)\n54\t\n55\tif TYPE_CHECKING:\n56\t    from .prd import PRD\n57\t    from .style import Styler\n58\t\n59\t\n60\tlogger = logging.getLogger(\"darkfactory.runner\")\n61\t\n62\t\n63\t@dataclass\n64\tclass TaskStep:\n65\t    \"\"\"A single executed task step and its outcome.\n66\t\n67\t    Used by :class:`RunResult` to record what actually happened during\n68\t    a workflow run, for both success reporting and debugging failures.\n69\t    \"\"\"\n70\t\n71\t    name: str\n72\t    kind: str  # \"builtin\" | \"agent\" | \"shell\"\n73\t    success: bool\n74\t    detail: str = \"\"\n75\t\n76\t\n77\t@dataclass\n78\tclass RunResult:\n79\t    \"\"\"Structured outcome of a workflow run.\n80\t\n81\t    The runner populates this as it walks the task list. On success,\n82\t    ``success=True`` and ``pr_url`` is set (assuming the workflow\n83\t    includes a ``create_pr`` built-in). On failure, ``success=False``\n84\t    and ``failure_reason`` describes what went wrong; ``steps`` is\n85\t    still populated with every step that completed before the failure.\n86\t    \"\"\"\n87\t\n88\t    success: bool\n89\t    pr_url: str | None = None\n90\t    steps: list[TaskStep] = field(default_factory=list)\n91\t    failure_reason: str | None = None\n92\t\n93\t\n94\tdef _compute_branch_name(prd: \"PRD\") -> str:\n95\t    \"\"\"Derive the branch name a workflow should use for this PRD.\n96\t\n97\t    Matches the convention in ``ensure_worktree``:\n98\t    ``prd/<id>-<slug>``. Surfaced as a helper so callers can compute\n99\t    it before creating the ExecutionContext.\n100\t    \"\"\"\n101\t    return f\"prd/{prd.id}-{prd.slug}\"\n102\t\n103\t\n104\tdef _pick_model(task: AgentTask, prd: \"PRD\", override: str | None = None) -> str:\n105\t    \"\"\"Resolve the model to use for an AgentTask invocation.\n106\t\n107\t    Priority: CLI override > task.model > capability-derived > sonnet.\n108\t    \"\"\"\n109\t    if override:\n110\t        return override\n111\t    if task.model:\n112\t        return task.model\n113\t    if task.model_from_capability:\n114\t        return capability_to_model(prd.capability)\n115\t    return \"sonnet\"\n116\t\n117\t\n118\tdef run_workflow(\n119\t    prd: \"PRD\",\n120\t    workflow: Workflow,\n121\t    repo_root: Path,\n122\t    base_ref: str,\n123\t    *,\n124\t    dry_run: bool = True,\n125\t    model_override: str | None = None,\n126\t    styler: \"Styler | None\" = None,\n127\t) -> RunResult:\n128\t    \"\"\"Execute a workflow against a single PRD and return the result.\n129\t\n130\t    Builds an :class:`ExecutionContext` and dispatches each task in\n131\t    ``workflow.tasks`` in order. Tasks mutate the context as they run\n132\t    (set worktree path, store agent output, capture PR URL). On any\n133\t    uncaught exception, returns a failure result with the partial\n134\t    ``steps`` list so the caller can see what completed.\n135\t\n136\t    ``dry_run=True`` (default) makes every task log instead of\n137\t    executing — safe to call on arbitrary PRDs.\n138\t    \"\"\"\n139\t    branch_name = _compute_branch_name(prd)\n140\t    ctx = ExecutionContext(\n141\t        prd=prd,\n142\t        repo_root=repo_root,\n143\t        workflow=workflow,\n144\t        base_ref=base_ref,\n145\t        branch_name=branch_name,\n146\t        cwd=repo_root,\n147\t        dry_run=dry_run,\n148\t        logger=logger,\n149\t    )\n150\t\n151\t    result = RunResult(success=True)\n152\t    # Track the last AgentTask so a later ShellTask with\n153\t    # on_failure=retry_agent can re-invoke it.\n154\t    last_agent_task: AgentTask | None = None\n155\t    last_agent_result: InvokeResult | None = None\n156\t\n157\t    try:\n158\t        for task in workflow.tasks:\n159\t            try:\n160\t                step = _dispatch(\n161\t                    task,\n162\t                    ctx,\n163\t                    model_override,\n164\t                    last_agent_task,\n165\t                    last_agent_result,\n166\t                    styler=styler,\n167\t                )\n168\t                result.steps.append(step)\n169\t\n170\t                if isinstance(task, AgentTask):\n171\t                    last_agent_task = task\n172\t                    # We can't easily reach the InvokeResult from _dispatch without\n173\t                    # restructuring, so we re-record it here via a side channel:\n174\t                    # _dispatch stores the agent result on the context.\n175\t                    last_agent_result = getattr(ctx, \"_last_agent_result\", None)\n176\t\n177\t                if not step.success:\n178\t                    result.success = False\n179\t                    result.failure_reason = step.detail or f\"task {step.name!r} failed\"\n180\t                    break\n181\t            except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001 — we want to log any failure\n182\t                result.success = False\n183\t                result.failure_reason = f\"task {_task_name(task)!r} raised: {exc}\"\n184\t                result.steps.append(\n185\t                    TaskStep(\n186\t                        name=_task_name(task),\n187\t                        kind=_task_kind(task),\n188\t                        success=False,\n189\t                        detail=str(exc),\n190\t                    )\n191\t                )\n192\t                break\n193\t    finally:\n194\t        _release_worktree_lock(ctx)\n195\t\n196\t    result.pr_url = ctx.pr_url\n197\t    return result\n198\t\n199\t\n200\tdef _release_worktree_lock(ctx: ExecutionContext) -> None:\n201\t    \"\"\"Release the advisory lock acquired by ensure_worktree, if any.\n202\t\n203\t    Safe to call multiple times and on contexts that never acquired a\n204\t    lock (e.g. dry-run paths).\n205\t    \"\"\"\n206\t    lock = ctx._worktree_lock\n207\t    if lock is None:\n208\t        return\n209\t    try:\n210\t        lock.release()\n211\t    except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001\n212\t        ctx.logger.warning(\"failed to release worktree lock: %s\", exc)\n213\t    finally:\n214\t        ctx._worktree_lock = None\n215\t\n216\t\n217\tdef _task_name(task: Task) -> str:\n218\t    if isinstance(task, BuiltIn):\n219\t        return task.name\n220\t    if isinstance(task, AgentTask):\n221\t        return task.name\n222\t    if isinstance(task, ShellTask):\n223\t        return task.name\n224\t    return type(task).__name__\n225\t\n226\t\n227\tdef _task_kind(task: Task) -> str:\n228\t    if isinstance(task, BuiltIn):\n229\t        return \"builtin\"\n230\t    if isinstance(task, AgentTask):\n231\t        return \"agent\"\n232\t    if isinstance(task, ShellTask):\n233\t        return \"shell\"\n234\t    return \"unknown\"\n235\t\n236\t\n237\tdef _dispatch(\n238\t    task: Task,\n239\t    ctx: ExecutionContext,\n240\t    model_override: str | None,\n241\t    last_agent_task: AgentTask | None,\n242\t    last_agent_result: InvokeResult | None,\n243\t    *,\n244\t    styler: \"Styler | None\" = None,\n245\t) -> TaskStep:\n246\t    \"\"\"Dispatch a single task by type and return a TaskStep describing the outcome.\"\"\"\n247\t    if isinstance(task, BuiltIn):\n248\t        return _run_builtin(task, ctx)\n249\t    if isinstance(task, AgentTask):\n250\t        return _run_agent(task, ctx, model_override, styler=styler)\n251\t    if isinstance(task, ShellTask):\n252\t        return _run_shell(task, ctx, last_agent_task, model_override, styler=styler)\n253\t    raise TypeError(f\"unknown task type: {type(task).__name__}\")\n254\t\n255\t\n256\tdef _run_builtin(task: BuiltIn, ctx: ExecutionContext) -> TaskStep:\n257\t    \"\"\"Look up the built-in by name and call it with formatted kwargs.\"\"\"\n258\t    if task.name not in BUILTINS:\n259\t        return TaskStep(\n260\t            name=task.name,\n261\t            kind=\"builtin\",\n262\t            success=False,\n263\t            detail=f\"no builtin registered for {task.name!r}\",\n264\t        )\n265\t\n266\t    func = BUILTINS[task.name]\n267\t\n268\t    # Format any string kwargs against the context (e.g. commit messages\n269\t    # like \"chore(prd): {prd_id} start work\").\n270\t    formatted_kwargs: dict[str, object] = {}\n271\t    for key, value in task.kwargs.items():\n272\t        if isinstance(value, str):\n273\t            formatted_kwargs[key] = ctx.format_string(value)\n274\t        else:\n275\t            formatted_kwargs[key] = value\n276\t\n277\t    func(ctx, **formatted_kwargs)\n278\t    return TaskStep(name=task.name, kind=\"builtin\", success=True)\n279\t\n280\t\n281\tdef _run_agent(\n282\t    task: AgentTask,\n283\t    ctx: ExecutionContext,\n284\t    model_override: str | None,\n285\t    *,\n286\t    extras: dict[str, object] | None = None,\n287\t    styler: \"Styler | None\" = None,\n288\t) -> TaskStep:\n289\t    \"\"\"Compose prompts, invoke Claude Code, and record the result on context.\"\"\"\n290\t    prompt = compose_prompt(ctx.workflow, task.prompts, ctx, extras=extras)\n291\t    model = _pick_model(task, ctx.prd, override=model_override)\n292\t\n293\t    result = invoke_claude(\n294\t        prompt=prompt,\n295\t        tools=task.tools,\n296\t        model=model,\n297\t        cwd=ctx.cwd,\n298\t        sentinel_success=task.sentinel_success,\n299\t        sentinel_failure=task.sentinel_failure,\n300\t        dry_run=ctx.dry_run,\n301\t        styler=styler,\n302\t    )\n303\t\n304\t    ctx.agent_output = result.stdout\n305\t    ctx.agent_success = result.success\n306\t    ctx.last_invoke_result = result\n307\t    ctx.model = model\n308\t    ctx.invoke_count += 1\n309\t    # Side channel for the retry-on-failure path — keeps the function\n310\t    # signature stable.\n311\t    setattr(ctx, \"_last_agent_result\", result)\n312\t\n313\t    # Dump the raw agent transcript to a file inside the worktree so any\n314\t    # 'no sentinel found' / 'unexpected output' failures can be diagnosed\n315\t    # post-mortem without re-running. The file lives at the worktree root\n316\t    # and is overwritten on each invocation (one transcript per agent\n317\t    # task per run). Diagnostic dump must never fail the workflow.\n318\t    if not ctx.dry_run and ctx.cwd:\n319\t        try:\n320\t            transcript = ctx.cwd / \".harness-agent-output.log\"\n321\t            transcript.write_text(\n322\t                \"\\n\".join(\n323\t                    [\n324\t                        f\"# task: {task.name}\",\n325\t                        f\"# model: {model}\",\n326\t                        f\"# success: {result.success}\",\n327\t                        f\"# exit_code: {result.exit_code}\",\n328\t                        f\"# failure_reason: {result.failure_reason or ''}\",\n329\t                        \"# ---- stdout ----\",\n330\t                        result.stdout,\n331\t                        \"# ---- stderr ----\",\n332\t                        result.stderr,\n333\t                        \"\",\n334\t                    ]\n335\t                ),\n336\t                encoding=\"utf-8\",\n337\t            )\n338\t        except OSError as exc:\n339\t            logger.warning(\"could not write agent transcript: %s\", exc)\n340\t\n341\t    return TaskStep(\n342\t        name=task.name,\n343\t        kind=\"agent\",\n344\t        success=result.success,\n345\t        detail=result.failure_reason or \"\",\n346\t    )\n347\t\n348\t\n349\tdef _run_shell(\n350\t    task: ShellTask,\n351\t    ctx: ExecutionContext,\n352\t    last_agent_task: AgentTask | None,\n353\t    model_override: str | None,\n354\t    *,\n355\t    styler: \"Styler | None\" = None,\n356\t) -> TaskStep:\n357\t    \"\"\"Run a shell command, handling on_failure policy with agent retry if configured.\"\"\"\n358\t    cmd = ctx.format_string(task.cmd)\n359\t\n360\t    if ctx.dry_run:\n361\t        ctx.logger.info(\"[dry-run] %s\", cmd)\n362\t        return TaskStep(name=task.name, kind=\"shell\", success=True, detail=\"dry-run\")\n363\t\n364\t    first_result = _run_shell_once(cmd, ctx, task.env)\n365\t\n366\t    if first_result.returncode == 0:\n367\t        return TaskStep(name=task.name, kind=\"shell\", success=True)\n368\t\n369\t    # Shell task failed — apply on_failure policy.\n370\t    failure_output = first_result.stdout + \"\\n\" + first_result.stderr\n371\t\n372\t    if task.on_failure == \"ignore\":\n373\t        ctx.logger.warning(\n374\t            \"shell task %r failed (ignored): exit=%d\",\n375\t            task.name,\n376\t            first_result.returncode,\n377\t        )\n378\t        return TaskStep(\n379\t            name=task.name,\n380\t            kind=\"shell\",\n381\t            success=True,\n382\t            detail=f\"ignored failure (exit {first_result.returncode})\",\n383\t        )\n384\t\n385\t    if task.on_failure == \"fail\" or last_agent_task is None:\n386\t        return TaskStep(\n387\t            name=task.name,\n388\t            kind=\"shell\",\n389\t            success=False,\n390\t            detail=f\"exit {first_result.returncode}: {failure_output.strip()[:500]}\",\n391\t        )\n392\t\n393\t    # on_failure == \"retry_agent\" and we have a prior AgentTask to re-invoke\n394\t    ctx.logger.info(\n395\t        \"shell task %r failed (exit %d); retrying via agent\",\n396\t        task.name,\n397\t        first_result.returncode,\n398\t    )\n399\t\n400\t    # Re-invoke the last AgentTask with verify_prompts + CHECK_OUTPUT\n401\t    agent_step = _run_agent(\n402\t        AgentTask(\n403\t            name=f\"{last_agent_task.name}-retry\",\n404\t            prompts=last_agent_task.verify_prompts or last_agent_task.prompts,\n405\t            tools=last_agent_task.tools,\n406\t            model=last_agent_task.model,\n407\t            model_from_capability=last_agent_task.model_from_capability,\n408\t            retries=0,\n409\t            sentinel_success=last_agent_task.sentinel_success,\n410\t            sentinel_failure=last_agent_task.sentinel_failure,\n411\t        ),\n412\t        ctx,\n413\t        model_override,\n414\t        extras={\"CHECK_OUTPUT\": failure_output},\n415\t        styler=styler,\n416\t    )\n417\t    if not agent_step.success:\n418\t        return TaskStep(\n419\t            name=task.name,\n420\t            kind=\"shell\",\n421\t            success=False,\n422\t            detail=f\"retry agent failed: {agent_step.detail}\",\n423\t        )\n424\t\n425\t    # Re-run the shell task once more after the agent fix\n426\t    second_result = _run_shell_once(cmd, ctx, task.env)\n427\t    if second_result.returncode == 0:\n428\t        return TaskStep(\n429\t            name=task.name,\n430\t            kind=\"shell\",\n431\t            success=True,\n432\t            detail=\"passed after agent retry\",\n433\t        )\n434\t\n435\t    return TaskStep(\n436\t        name=task.name,\n437\t        kind=\"shell\",\n438\t        success=False,\n439\t        detail=(\n440\t            f\"still failing after agent retry (exit {second_result.returncode}): \"\n441\t            f\"{(second_result.stdout + second_result.stderr).strip()[:500]}\"\n442\t        ),\n443\t    )\n444\t\n445\t\n446\tdef _run_shell_once(\n447\t    cmd: str,\n448\t    ctx: ExecutionContext,\n449\t    env: dict[str, str],\n450\t) -> subprocess.CompletedProcess[str]:\n451\t    \"\"\"Run a shell command once and return the completed-process result.\"\"\"\n452\t    import os\n453\t\n454\t    full_env = dict(os.environ)\n455\t    full_env.update(env)\n456\t\n457\t    return subprocess.run(\n458\t        cmd,\n459\t        shell=True,\n460\t        cwd=str(ctx.cwd),\n461\t        capture_output=True,\n462\t        text=True,\n463\t        env=full_env,\n464\t        check=False,\n465\t    )\n466\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"486cefb7-8454-4ea9-8512-7a451e5c819b","uuid":"520c96da-206d-414b-88cd-f3edbf5fb316","timestamp":"2026-04-08T16:23:18.769Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.worktrees/PRD-224.6-commit-transcript/src/darkfactory/runner.py","content":"\"\"\"Workflow execution engine — walks a workflow's tasks against a context.\n\nThe runner is the glue between every other module in the harness:\n\n- It holds an :class:`~darkfactory.workflow.ExecutionContext` and\n  threads it through the task list.\n- For each :class:`~darkfactory.workflow.BuiltIn`, it looks up the\n  named function in :data:`~darkfactory.builtins.BUILTINS` and calls\n  it with the context + formatted kwargs.\n- For each :class:`~darkfactory.workflow.AgentTask`, it composes the\n  prompt via :func:`~darkfactory.templates.compose_prompt`, picks the\n  model (explicit override > capability mapping > sonnet fallback),\n  invokes Claude Code via :func:`~darkfactory.invoke.invoke_claude`,\n  and stores the output on the context.\n- For each :class:`~darkfactory.workflow.ShellTask`, it runs the\n  formatted command and handles the configured ``on_failure`` policy.\n\nThe runner does **not** know how to create branches, manage\nworktrees, or open PRs — those are built-in tasks. Its only job is\nthe dispatch loop and the retry-on-failure bookkeeping.\n\nRetry semantics: when a ShellTask fails with\n``on_failure=\"retry_agent\"``, the runner looks backward in the task\nlist for the most recent AgentTask, re-invokes it with the failed\noutput bound to ``{{CHECK_OUTPUT}}``, and re-runs the failed shell\ntask once. If it still fails, the runner gives up and marks the\nPRD blocked (via a separate ``set_status`` built-in call).\n\nDry-run mode: when ``ctx.dry_run=True``, every built-in and shell\ntask logs what it would do without executing. Agent tasks return a\nsynthetic success result via :func:`~darkfactory.invoke.invoke_claude`'s\n``dry_run=True`` path. This is what ``prd plan`` uses.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport logging\nimport subprocess\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import TYPE_CHECKING\n\nfrom .builtins import BUILTINS\nfrom .invoke import InvokeResult, capability_to_model, invoke_claude\nfrom .templates import compose_prompt\nfrom .workflow import (\n    AgentTask,\n    BuiltIn,\n    ExecutionContext,\n    ShellTask,\n    Task,\n    Workflow,\n)\n\nif TYPE_CHECKING:\n    from .prd import PRD\n    from .style import Styler\n\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(\"darkfactory.runner\")\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass TaskStep:\n    \"\"\"A single executed task step and its outcome.\n\n    Used by :class:`RunResult` to record what actually happened during\n    a workflow run, for both success reporting and debugging failures.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    name: str\n    kind: str  # \"builtin\" | \"agent\" | \"shell\"\n    success: bool\n    detail: str = \"\"\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass RunResult:\n    \"\"\"Structured outcome of a workflow run.\n\n    The runner populates this as it walks the task list. On success,\n    ``success=True`` and ``pr_url`` is set (assuming the workflow\n    includes a ``create_pr`` built-in). On failure, ``success=False``\n    and ``failure_reason`` describes what went wrong; ``steps`` is\n    still populated with every step that completed before the failure.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    success: bool\n    pr_url: str | None = None\n    steps: list[TaskStep] = field(default_factory=list)\n    failure_reason: str | None = None\n\n\ndef _compute_branch_name(prd: \"PRD\") -> str:\n    \"\"\"Derive the branch name a workflow should use for this PRD.\n\n    Matches the convention in ``ensure_worktree``:\n    ``prd/<id>-<slug>``. Surfaced as a helper so callers can compute\n    it before creating the ExecutionContext.\n    \"\"\"\n    return f\"prd/{prd.id}-{prd.slug}\"\n\n\ndef _pick_model(task: AgentTask, prd: \"PRD\", override: str | None = None) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Resolve the model to use for an AgentTask invocation.\n\n    Priority: CLI override > task.model > capability-derived > sonnet.\n    \"\"\"\n    if override:\n        return override\n    if task.model:\n        return task.model\n    if task.model_from_capability:\n        return capability_to_model(prd.capability)\n    return \"sonnet\"\n\n\ndef run_workflow(\n    prd: \"PRD\",\n    workflow: Workflow,\n    repo_root: Path,\n    base_ref: str,\n    *,\n    dry_run: bool = True,\n    model_override: str | None = None,\n    styler: \"Styler | None\" = None,\n) -> RunResult:\n    \"\"\"Execute a workflow against a single PRD and return the result.\n\n    Builds an :class:`ExecutionContext` and dispatches each task in\n    ``workflow.tasks`` in order. Tasks mutate the context as they run\n    (set worktree path, store agent output, capture PR URL). On any\n    uncaught exception, returns a failure result with the partial\n    ``steps`` list so the caller can see what completed.\n\n    ``dry_run=True`` (default) makes every task log instead of\n    executing — safe to call on arbitrary PRDs.\n    \"\"\"\n    branch_name = _compute_branch_name(prd)\n    ctx = ExecutionContext(\n        prd=prd,\n        repo_root=repo_root,\n        workflow=workflow,\n        base_ref=base_ref,\n        branch_name=branch_name,\n        cwd=repo_root,\n        dry_run=dry_run,\n        logger=logger,\n    )\n\n    result = RunResult(success=True)\n    # Track the last AgentTask so a later ShellTask with\n    # on_failure=retry_agent can re-invoke it.\n    last_agent_task: AgentTask | None = None\n    last_agent_result: InvokeResult | None = None\n\n    try:\n        for task in workflow.tasks:\n            try:\n                step = _dispatch(\n                    task,\n                    ctx,\n                    model_override,\n                    last_agent_task,\n                    last_agent_result,\n                    styler=styler,\n                )\n                result.steps.append(step)\n\n                if isinstance(task, AgentTask):\n                    last_agent_task = task\n                    # We can't easily reach the InvokeResult from _dispatch without\n                    # restructuring, so we re-record it here via a side channel:\n                    # _dispatch stores the agent result on the context.\n                    last_agent_result = getattr(ctx, \"_last_agent_result\", None)\n\n                if not step.success:\n                    result.success = False\n                    result.failure_reason = step.detail or f\"task {step.name!r} failed\"\n                    break\n            except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001 — we want to log any failure\n                result.success = False\n                result.failure_reason = f\"task {_task_name(task)!r} raised: {exc}\"\n                result.steps.append(\n                    TaskStep(\n                        name=_task_name(task),\n                        kind=_task_kind(task),\n                        success=False,\n                        detail=str(exc),\n                    )\n                )\n                break\n    finally:\n        _release_worktree_lock(ctx)\n\n    result.pr_url = ctx.pr_url\n    return result\n\n\ndef _release_worktree_lock(ctx: ExecutionContext) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Release the advisory lock acquired by ensure_worktree, if any.\n\n    Safe to call multiple times and on contexts that never acquired a\n    lock (e.g. dry-run paths).\n    \"\"\"\n    lock = ctx._worktree_lock\n    if lock is None:\n        return\n    try:\n        lock.release()\n    except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001\n        ctx.logger.warning(\"failed to release worktree lock: %s\", exc)\n    finally:\n        ctx._worktree_lock = None\n\n\ndef _task_name(task: Task) -> str:\n    if isinstance(task, BuiltIn):\n        return task.name\n    if isinstance(task, AgentTask):\n        return task.name\n    if isinstance(task, ShellTask):\n        return task.name\n    return type(task).__name__\n\n\ndef _task_kind(task: Task) -> str:\n    if isinstance(task, BuiltIn):\n        return \"builtin\"\n    if isinstance(task, AgentTask):\n        return \"agent\"\n    if isinstance(task, ShellTask):\n        return \"shell\"\n    return \"unknown\"\n\n\ndef _dispatch(\n    task: Task,\n    ctx: ExecutionContext,\n    model_override: str | None,\n    last_agent_task: AgentTask | None,\n    last_agent_result: InvokeResult | None,\n    *,\n    styler: \"Styler | None\" = None,\n) -> TaskStep:\n    \"\"\"Dispatch a single task by type and return a TaskStep describing the outcome.\"\"\"\n    if isinstance(task, BuiltIn):\n        return _run_builtin(task, ctx)\n    if isinstance(task, AgentTask):\n        return _run_agent(task, ctx, model_override, styler=styler)\n    if isinstance(task, ShellTask):\n        return _run_shell(task, ctx, last_agent_task, model_override, styler=styler)\n    raise TypeError(f\"unknown task type: {type(task).__name__}\")\n\n\ndef _run_builtin(task: BuiltIn, ctx: ExecutionContext) -> TaskStep:\n    \"\"\"Look up the built-in by name and call it with formatted kwargs.\"\"\"\n    if task.name not in BUILTINS:\n        return TaskStep(\n            name=task.name,\n            kind=\"builtin\",\n            success=False,\n            detail=f\"no builtin registered for {task.name!r}\",\n        )\n\n    func = BUILTINS[task.name]\n\n    # Format any string kwargs against the context (e.g. commit messages\n    # like \"chore(prd): {prd_id} start work\").\n    formatted_kwargs: dict[str, object] = {}\n    for key, value in task.kwargs.items():\n        if isinstance(value, str):\n            formatted_kwargs[key] = ctx.format_string(value)\n        else:\n            formatted_kwargs[key] = value\n\n    func(ctx, **formatted_kwargs)\n    return TaskStep(name=task.name, kind=\"builtin\", success=True)\n\n\ndef _run_agent(\n    task: AgentTask,\n    ctx: ExecutionContext,\n    model_override: str | None,\n    *,\n    extras: dict[str, object] | None = None,\n    styler: \"Styler | None\" = None,\n) -> TaskStep:\n    \"\"\"Compose prompts, invoke Claude Code, and record the result on context.\"\"\"\n    prompt = compose_prompt(ctx.workflow, task.prompts, ctx, extras=extras)\n    model = _pick_model(task, ctx.prd, override=model_override)\n\n    result = invoke_claude(\n        prompt=prompt,\n        tools=task.tools,\n        model=model,\n        cwd=ctx.cwd,\n        sentinel_success=task.sentinel_success,\n        sentinel_failure=task.sentinel_failure,\n        dry_run=ctx.dry_run,\n        styler=styler,\n    )\n\n    ctx.agent_output = result.stdout\n    ctx.agent_success = result.success\n    ctx.last_invoke_result = result\n    ctx.model = model\n    ctx.invoke_count += 1\n    # Side channel for the retry-on-failure path — keeps the function\n    # signature stable.\n    setattr(ctx, \"_last_agent_result\", result)\n\n    # Dump the raw agent transcript to a file inside the worktree so any\n    # 'no sentinel found' / 'unexpected output' failures can be diagnosed\n    # post-mortem without re-running. The file lives at the worktree root\n    # and is overwritten on each invocation (one transcript per agent\n    # task per run). Diagnostic dump must never fail the workflow.\n    if not ctx.dry_run and ctx.cwd:\n        try:\n            transcript = ctx.cwd / \".harness-agent-output.log\"\n            transcript.write_text(\n                \"\\n\".join(\n                    [\n                        f\"# task: {task.name}\",\n                        f\"# model: {model}\",\n                        f\"# success: {result.success}\",\n                        f\"# exit_code: {result.exit_code}\",\n                        f\"# failure_reason: {result.failure_reason or ''}\",\n                        \"# ---- stdout ----\",\n                        result.stdout,\n                        \"# ---- stderr ----\",\n                        result.stderr,\n                        \"\",\n                    ]\n                ),\n                encoding=\"utf-8\",\n            )\n        except OSError as exc:\n            logger.warning(\"could not write agent transcript: %s\", exc)\n\n    return TaskStep(\n        name=task.name,\n        kind=\"agent\",\n        success=result.success,\n        detail=result.failure_reason or \"\",\n    )\n\n\ndef _run_shell(\n    task: ShellTask,\n    ctx: ExecutionContext,\n    last_agent_task: AgentTask | None,\n    model_override: str | None,\n    *,\n    styler: \"Styler | None\" = None,\n) -> TaskStep:\n    \"\"\"Run a shell command, handling on_failure policy with agent retry if configured.\"\"\"\n    cmd = ctx.format_string(task.cmd)\n\n    if ctx.dry_run:\n        ctx.logger.info(\"[dry-run] %s\", cmd)\n        return TaskStep(name=task.name, kind=\"shell\", success=True, detail=\"dry-run\")\n\n    first_result = _run_shell_once(cmd, ctx, task.env)\n\n    if first_result.returncode == 0:\n        return TaskStep(name=task.name, kind=\"shell\", success=True)\n\n    # Shell task failed — apply on_failure policy.\n    failure_output = first_result.stdout + \"\\n\" + first_result.stderr\n\n    if task.on_failure == \"ignore\":\n        ctx.logger.warning(\n            \"shell task %r failed (ignored): exit=%d\",\n            task.name,\n            first_result.returncode,\n        )\n        return TaskStep(\n            name=task.name,\n            kind=\"shell\",\n            success=True,\n            detail=f\"ignored failure (exit {first_result.returncode})\",\n        )\n\n    if task.on_failure == \"fail\" or last_agent_task is None:\n        return TaskStep(\n            name=task.name,\n            kind=\"shell\",\n            success=False,\n            detail=f\"exit {first_result.returncode}: {failure_output.strip()[:500]}\",\n        )\n\n    # on_failure == \"retry_agent\" and we have a prior AgentTask to re-invoke\n    ctx.logger.info(\n        \"shell task %r failed (exit %d); retrying via agent\",\n        task.name,\n        first_result.returncode,\n    )\n\n    # Re-invoke the last AgentTask with verify_prompts + CHECK_OUTPUT\n    agent_step = _run_agent(\n        AgentTask(\n            name=f\"{last_agent_task.name}-retry\",\n            prompts=last_agent_task.verify_prompts or last_agent_task.prompts,\n            tools=last_agent_task.tools,\n            model=last_agent_task.model,\n            model_from_capability=last_agent_task.model_from_capability,\n            retries=0,\n            sentinel_success=last_agent_task.sentinel_success,\n            sentinel_failure=last_agent_task.sentinel_failure,\n        ),\n        ctx,\n        model_override,\n        extras={\"CHECK_OUTPUT\": failure_output},\n        styler=styler,\n    )\n    if not agent_step.success:\n        return TaskStep(\n            name=task.name,\n            kind=\"shell\",\n            success=False,\n            detail=f\"retry agent failed: {agent_step.detail}\",\n        )\n\n    # Re-run the shell task once more after the agent fix\n    second_result = _run_shell_once(cmd, ctx, task.env)\n    if second_result.returncode == 0:\n        return TaskStep(\n            name=task.name,\n            kind=\"shell\",\n            success=True,\n            detail=\"passed after agent retry\",\n        )\n\n    return TaskStep(\n        name=task.name,\n        kind=\"shell\",\n        success=False,\n        detail=(\n            f\"still failing after agent retry (exit {second_result.returncode}): \"\n            f\"{(second_result.stdout + second_result.stderr).strip()[:500]}\"\n        ),\n    )\n\n\ndef _run_shell_once(\n    cmd: str,\n    ctx: ExecutionContext,\n    env: dict[str, str],\n) -> subprocess.CompletedProcess[str]:\n    \"\"\"Run a shell command once and return the completed-process result.\"\"\"\n    import os\n\n    full_env = dict(os.environ)\n    full_env.update(env)\n\n    return subprocess.run(\n        cmd,\n        shell=True,\n        cwd=str(ctx.cwd),\n        capture_output=True,\n        text=True,\n        env=full_env,\n        check=False,\n    )\n","numLines":466,"startLine":1,"totalLines":466}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017xVXpNNC4nk8Zu1GY4zg3U","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"Declarative workflow definitions for the PRD harness.\n2\t\n3\tA ``Workflow`` is a named, ordered list of ``Task`` s that implement one\n4\tkind of PRD. Three task types compose a workflow:\n5\t\n6\t- :class:`BuiltIn` — reference a deterministic primitive by name. The\n7\t  set is fixed by the harness package (``builtins.py``): ``ensure_worktree``,\n8\t  ``set_status``, ``commit``, ``push_branch``, ``create_pr``, etc.\n9\t- :class:`AgentTask` — invoke Claude Code with composed prompts, a tool\n10\t  allowlist, and a model selection. This is the only task type where\n11\t  actual code gets written.\n12\t- :class:`ShellTask` — run a deterministic shell command inside the\n13\t  worktree. Used for verification (``just test``, ``pnpm storybook:build``)\n14\t  with an ``on_failure`` policy.\n15\t\n16\tWorkflows live in ``tools/prd-harness/workflows/<name>/workflow.py`` modules\n17\tthat export a top-level ``workflow`` attribute. The loader discovers them\n18\tand the runner dispatches each task in order against an\n19\t:class:`ExecutionContext` that threads mutable state (worktree path, branch\n20\tname, agent output, PR URL, etc.) between tasks.\n21\t\n22\tThis module intentionally contains no I/O, no subprocess calls, and no\n23\tdependency on ``prd.py`` at import time. It's pure data — the shapes that\n24\tworkflow authors and the runner both plug into.\n25\t\"\"\"\n26\t\n27\tfrom __future__ import annotations\n28\t\n29\timport logging\n30\tfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\n31\tfrom pathlib import Path\n32\tfrom typing import TYPE_CHECKING, Any, Callable, Literal\n33\t\n34\tif TYPE_CHECKING:\n35\t    from filelock import FileLock\n36\t\n37\t    from .invoke import InvokeResult\n38\t    from .prd import PRD\n39\t\n40\t\n41\t# ---------- type aliases ----------\n42\t\n43\t\n44\tOnFailure = Literal[\"fail\", \"retry_agent\", \"ignore\"]\n45\t\"\"\"Policy for a :class:`ShellTask` when the command exits non-zero.\n46\t\n47\t- ``\"fail\"``: abort the workflow with an error (default).\n48\t- ``\"retry_agent\"``: re-invoke the preceding :class:`AgentTask` once with\n49\t  the verify prompts and the failed check output, then retry the shell\n50\t  task once. If it still fails, abort.\n51\t- ``\"ignore\"``: log the failure and continue with the next task. Useful\n52\t  for advisory checks that shouldn't block progress.\n53\t\"\"\"\n54\t\n55\t\n56\tStatus = Literal[\n57\t    \"draft\", \"ready\", \"in-progress\", \"review\", \"done\", \"blocked\", \"cancelled\"\n58\t]\n59\t\"\"\"All PRD lifecycle statuses. Mirrors the enum in ``docs/prd/_schema.yaml``.\"\"\"\n60\t\n61\t\n62\tAppliesToPredicate = Callable[[\"PRD\", dict[str, \"PRD\"]], bool]\n63\t\"\"\"Two-argument predicate deciding whether a workflow applies to a PRD.\n64\t\n65\tTakes the target PRD plus the full PRD set so predicates that need\n66\tsibling or ancestor context (e.g. ``planning`` checking\n67\t``is_fully_decomposed``) can reach for it. Simple predicates like\n68\t``lambda prd, prds: \"ui\" in prd.tags`` ignore the second argument.\n69\t\"\"\"\n70\t\n71\t\n72\t# ---------- Task hierarchy ----------\n73\t\n74\t\n75\tclass Task:\n76\t    \"\"\"Marker base class for all task types.\n77\t\n78\t    Deliberately not a ``@dataclass`` — subclasses define their own fields\n79\t    and don't share any, so dataclass inheritance would add complexity with\n80\t    no benefit. The class exists purely for ``isinstance()`` dispatch in\n81\t    the runner's task loop.\n82\t    \"\"\"\n83\t\n84\t\n85\t@dataclass\n86\tclass BuiltIn(Task):\n87\t    \"\"\"Reference a deterministic primitive from the ``BUILTINS`` registry.\n88\t\n89\t    The runner looks up ``name`` in ``darkfactory.builtins.BUILTINS`` and\n90\t    calls the registered function with ``(ctx, **kwargs)``. String values\n91\t    in ``kwargs`` are formatted via :meth:`ExecutionContext.format_string`\n92\t    before the call, so workflow authors can use ``{prd_id}``-style\n93\t    placeholders.\n94\t\n95\t    Example::\n96\t\n97\t        BuiltIn(\"commit\", kwargs={\"message\": \"chore(prd): {prd_id} start work\"})\n98\t\n99\t    The runner resolves ``{prd_id}`` at execution time; the workflow\n100\t    definition stays free of runtime state.\n101\t    \"\"\"\n102\t\n103\t    name: str\n104\t    kwargs: dict[str, Any] = field(default_factory=dict)\n105\t\n106\t\n107\t@dataclass\n108\tclass AgentTask(Task):\n109\t    \"\"\"Invoke Claude Code with composed prompts and a restricted tool allowlist.\n110\t\n111\t    The runner (see ``runner.py``) performs these steps:\n112\t\n113\t    1. Read each path in :attr:`prompts` relative to the workflow's\n114\t       directory (set by the loader) and concatenate the file contents.\n115\t    2. Substitute ``{{PRD_ID}}``/``{{PRD_TITLE}}``/``{{PRD_PATH}}``/etc.\n116\t       placeholders against the :class:`ExecutionContext` via\n117\t       ``templates.substitute_placeholders``.\n118\t    3. Pick a model: :attr:`model` if explicitly set, else map from\n119\t       ``ctx.prd.capability`` when :attr:`model_from_capability` is\n120\t       true, else fall back to sonnet.\n121\t    4. Pipe the composed prompt to ``claude --print`` via subprocess with\n122\t       ``--allowed-tools`` set to :attr:`tools`.\n123\t    5. Parse stdout for :attr:`sentinel_success` or :attr:`sentinel_failure`\n124\t       to decide whether the task succeeded. The agent is contracted to\n125\t       emit one of these as its final line.\n126\t\n127\t    When a subsequent :class:`ShellTask` fails with\n128\t    ``on_failure=\"retry_agent\"``, the runner re-invokes this AgentTask\n129\t    with :attr:`verify_prompts` prepended to the prompt list and\n130\t    ``{{CHECK_OUTPUT}}`` bound to the failed stdout/stderr — at most\n131\t    :attr:`retries` times.\n132\t    \"\"\"\n133\t\n134\t    name: str = \"implement\"\n135\t    prompts: list[str] = field(default_factory=list)\n136\t    tools: list[str] = field(default_factory=list)\n137\t    model: str | None = None\n138\t    model_from_capability: bool = True\n139\t    retries: int = 1\n140\t    verify_prompts: list[str] = field(default_factory=list)\n141\t    sentinel_success: str = \"PRD_EXECUTE_OK\"\n142\t    sentinel_failure: str = \"PRD_EXECUTE_FAILED\"\n143\t\n144\t\n145\t@dataclass\n146\tclass ShellTask(Task):\n147\t    \"\"\"Run a deterministic shell command inside the worktree.\n148\t\n149\t    ``cmd`` is formatted via :meth:`ExecutionContext.format_string` before\n150\t    execution (so ``{worktree}`` etc. placeholders are expanded) and runs\n151\t    with ``cwd=ctx.cwd`` (the worktree path after ``ensure_worktree``).\n152\t    ``env`` is merged into the subprocess environment.\n153\t\n154\t    :attr:`on_failure` controls the recovery path on non-zero exit. See\n155\t    the :data:`OnFailure` type alias for policy semantics.\n156\t    \"\"\"\n157\t\n158\t    name: str\n159\t    cmd: str\n160\t    on_failure: OnFailure = \"fail\"\n161\t    env: dict[str, str] = field(default_factory=dict)\n162\t\n163\t\n164\t# ---------- Workflow ----------\n165\t\n166\t\n167\tdef _default_applies_to(prd: \"PRD\", prds: dict[str, \"PRD\"]) -> bool:\n168\t    \"\"\"Default ``applies_to`` predicate — matches nothing.\n169\t\n170\t    Concrete workflows override this in their ``workflow.py`` module.\n171\t    Kept as a module-level function rather than a lambda so mypy and\n172\t    pickling (if ever needed) both behave.\n173\t    \"\"\"\n174\t    return False\n175\t\n176\t\n177\t@dataclass\n178\tclass Workflow:\n179\t    \"\"\"A named recipe for implementing one kind of PRD.\n180\t\n181\t    Authored in ``tools/prd-harness/workflows/<name>/workflow.py`` as a\n182\t    module-level ``workflow = Workflow(...)`` attribute. The loader\n183\t    discovers it, imports the module, and sets :attr:`workflow_dir` to\n184\t    the subdirectory path so AgentTask prompt paths resolve correctly.\n185\t\n186\t    :attr:`priority` orders workflows during assignment: higher numbers\n187\t    win when multiple predicates match. ``default`` has priority 0 and\n188\t    acts as a catchall. Ties are broken alphabetically by name.\n189\t    \"\"\"\n190\t\n191\t    name: str\n192\t    description: str = \"\"\n193\t    applies_to: AppliesToPredicate = field(default=_default_applies_to)\n194\t    priority: int = 0\n195\t    tasks: list[Task] = field(default_factory=list)\n196\t    workflow_dir: Path | None = None\n197\t\n198\t\n199\t# ---------- ExecutionContext ----------\n200\t\n201\t\n202\t@dataclass\n203\tclass ExecutionContext:\n204\t    \"\"\"State threaded through every task during a workflow run.\n205\t\n206\t    Tasks mutate this object in place as the workflow progresses:\n207\t\n208\t    - ``ensure_worktree`` sets :attr:`worktree_path` and :attr:`cwd`\n209\t    - The agent invoke populates :attr:`agent_output` and\n210\t      :attr:`agent_success`\n211\t    - ``create_pr`` sets :attr:`pr_url`\n212\t\n213\t    The runner creates one context at the start of ``run_workflow`` and\n214\t    passes it to each task in order. Tasks read from it (for formatting\n215\t    commit messages, composing prompts, etc.) and write to it (to record\n216\t    side effects for downstream tasks or the CLI to surface).\n217\t\n218\t    :attr:`dry_run` tells builtins, shell tasks, and the agent invoke to\n219\t    log what they WOULD do without actually invoking subprocesses, git,\n220\t    or gh. Drives the ``prd plan`` output.\n221\t    \"\"\"\n222\t\n223\t    prd: \"PRD\"\n224\t    repo_root: Path\n225\t    workflow: Workflow\n226\t    base_ref: str\n227\t    branch_name: str\n228\t    worktree_path: Path | None = None\n229\t    cwd: Path = field(default_factory=Path.cwd)\n230\t    agent_output: str | None = None\n231\t    agent_success: bool = False\n232\t    pr_url: str | None = None\n233\t    run_summary: str | None = None\n234\t    last_invoke_result: \"InvokeResult | None\" = None\n235\t    model: str | None = None\n236\t    invoke_count: int = 0\n237\t    dry_run: bool = True\n238\t    logger: logging.Logger = field(\n239\t        default_factory=lambda: logging.getLogger(\"darkfactory\")\n240\t    )\n241\t    # Advisory process-level lock held by ensure_worktree for the\n242\t    # lifetime of this run. Managed by builtins + runner; tests should\n243\t    # not touch it directly.\n244\t    _worktree_lock: \"FileLock | None\" = field(default=None, repr=False)\n245\t\n246\t    def format_string(self, template: str) -> str:\n247\t        \"\"\"Expand ``{placeholder}`` tokens against context state.\n248\t\n249\t        Supported placeholders:\n250\t\n251\t        - ``{prd_id}`` — the PRD's id (e.g. ``PRD-070``)\n252\t        - ``{prd_title}`` — the PRD's title\n253\t        - ``{prd_slug}`` — the slug portion of the PRD filename\n254\t        - ``{branch}`` — the current branch name\n255\t        - ``{base_ref}`` — the base ref the branch was created from\n256\t        - ``{worktree}`` — the worktree path as a string, or ``\"\"`` if\n257\t          the worktree hasn't been created yet\n258\t\n259\t        Unknown placeholders raise ``KeyError`` (intentionally strict —\n260\t        workflow authors should catch typos early). Contrast with the\n261\t        agent prompt templater in ``templates.py``, which leaves unknown\n262\t        placeholders unchanged to allow incremental template evolution.\n263\t        \"\"\"\n264\t        return template.format(\n265\t            prd_id=self.prd.id,\n266\t            prd_title=self.prd.title,\n267\t            prd_slug=self.prd.slug,\n268\t            branch=self.branch_name,\n269\t            base_ref=self.base_ref,\n270\t            worktree=str(self.worktree_path) if self.worktree_path else \"\",\n271\t        )\n272\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"486cefb7-8454-4ea9-8512-7a451e5c819b","uuid":"9c7bbce5-30dd-41e1-b541-941d9dc0d016","timestamp":"2026-04-08T16:23:18.960Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.worktrees/PRD-224.6-commit-transcript/src/darkfactory/workflow.py","content":"\"\"\"Declarative workflow definitions for the PRD harness.\n\nA ``Workflow`` is a named, ordered list of ``Task`` s that implement one\nkind of PRD. Three task types compose a workflow:\n\n- :class:`BuiltIn` — reference a deterministic primitive by name. The\n  set is fixed by the harness package (``builtins.py``): ``ensure_worktree``,\n  ``set_status``, ``commit``, ``push_branch``, ``create_pr``, etc.\n- :class:`AgentTask` — invoke Claude Code with composed prompts, a tool\n  allowlist, and a model selection. This is the only task type where\n  actual code gets written.\n- :class:`ShellTask` — run a deterministic shell command inside the\n  worktree. Used for verification (``just test``, ``pnpm storybook:build``)\n  with an ``on_failure`` policy.\n\nWorkflows live in ``tools/prd-harness/workflows/<name>/workflow.py`` modules\nthat export a top-level ``workflow`` attribute. The loader discovers them\nand the runner dispatches each task in order against an\n:class:`ExecutionContext` that threads mutable state (worktree path, branch\nname, agent output, PR URL, etc.) between tasks.\n\nThis module intentionally contains no I/O, no subprocess calls, and no\ndependency on ``prd.py`` at import time. It's pure data — the shapes that\nworkflow authors and the runner both plug into.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport logging\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import TYPE_CHECKING, Any, Callable, Literal\n\nif TYPE_CHECKING:\n    from filelock import FileLock\n\n    from .invoke import InvokeResult\n    from .prd import PRD\n\n\n# ---------- type aliases ----------\n\n\nOnFailure = Literal[\"fail\", \"retry_agent\", \"ignore\"]\n\"\"\"Policy for a :class:`ShellTask` when the command exits non-zero.\n\n- ``\"fail\"``: abort the workflow with an error (default).\n- ``\"retry_agent\"``: re-invoke the preceding :class:`AgentTask` once with\n  the verify prompts and the failed check output, then retry the shell\n  task once. If it still fails, abort.\n- ``\"ignore\"``: log the failure and continue with the next task. Useful\n  for advisory checks that shouldn't block progress.\n\"\"\"\n\n\nStatus = Literal[\n    \"draft\", \"ready\", \"in-progress\", \"review\", \"done\", \"blocked\", \"cancelled\"\n]\n\"\"\"All PRD lifecycle statuses. Mirrors the enum in ``docs/prd/_schema.yaml``.\"\"\"\n\n\nAppliesToPredicate = Callable[[\"PRD\", dict[str, \"PRD\"]], bool]\n\"\"\"Two-argument predicate deciding whether a workflow applies to a PRD.\n\nTakes the target PRD plus the full PRD set so predicates that need\nsibling or ancestor context (e.g. ``planning`` checking\n``is_fully_decomposed``) can reach for it. Simple predicates like\n``lambda prd, prds: \"ui\" in prd.tags`` ignore the second argument.\n\"\"\"\n\n\n# ---------- Task hierarchy ----------\n\n\nclass Task:\n    \"\"\"Marker base class for all task types.\n\n    Deliberately not a ``@dataclass`` — subclasses define their own fields\n    and don't share any, so dataclass inheritance would add complexity with\n    no benefit. The class exists purely for ``isinstance()`` dispatch in\n    the runner's task loop.\n    \"\"\"\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass BuiltIn(Task):\n    \"\"\"Reference a deterministic primitive from the ``BUILTINS`` registry.\n\n    The runner looks up ``name`` in ``darkfactory.builtins.BUILTINS`` and\n    calls the registered function with ``(ctx, **kwargs)``. String values\n    in ``kwargs`` are formatted via :meth:`ExecutionContext.format_string`\n    before the call, so workflow authors can use ``{prd_id}``-style\n    placeholders.\n\n    Example::\n\n        BuiltIn(\"commit\", kwargs={\"message\": \"chore(prd): {prd_id} start work\"})\n\n    The runner resolves ``{prd_id}`` at execution time; the workflow\n    definition stays free of runtime state.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    name: str\n    kwargs: dict[str, Any] = field(default_factory=dict)\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass AgentTask(Task):\n    \"\"\"Invoke Claude Code with composed prompts and a restricted tool allowlist.\n\n    The runner (see ``runner.py``) performs these steps:\n\n    1. Read each path in :attr:`prompts` relative to the workflow's\n       directory (set by the loader) and concatenate the file contents.\n    2. Substitute ``{{PRD_ID}}``/``{{PRD_TITLE}}``/``{{PRD_PATH}}``/etc.\n       placeholders against the :class:`ExecutionContext` via\n       ``templates.substitute_placeholders``.\n    3. Pick a model: :attr:`model` if explicitly set, else map from\n       ``ctx.prd.capability`` when :attr:`model_from_capability` is\n       true, else fall back to sonnet.\n    4. Pipe the composed prompt to ``claude --print`` via subprocess with\n       ``--allowed-tools`` set to :attr:`tools`.\n    5. Parse stdout for :attr:`sentinel_success` or :attr:`sentinel_failure`\n       to decide whether the task succeeded. The agent is contracted to\n       emit one of these as its final line.\n\n    When a subsequent :class:`ShellTask` fails with\n    ``on_failure=\"retry_agent\"``, the runner re-invokes this AgentTask\n    with :attr:`verify_prompts` prepended to the prompt list and\n    ``{{CHECK_OUTPUT}}`` bound to the failed stdout/stderr — at most\n    :attr:`retries` times.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    name: str = \"implement\"\n    prompts: list[str] = field(default_factory=list)\n    tools: list[str] = field(default_factory=list)\n    model: str | None = None\n    model_from_capability: bool = True\n    retries: int = 1\n    verify_prompts: list[str] = field(default_factory=list)\n    sentinel_success: str = \"PRD_EXECUTE_OK\"\n    sentinel_failure: str = \"PRD_EXECUTE_FAILED\"\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass ShellTask(Task):\n    \"\"\"Run a deterministic shell command inside the worktree.\n\n    ``cmd`` is formatted via :meth:`ExecutionContext.format_string` before\n    execution (so ``{worktree}`` etc. placeholders are expanded) and runs\n    with ``cwd=ctx.cwd`` (the worktree path after ``ensure_worktree``).\n    ``env`` is merged into the subprocess environment.\n\n    :attr:`on_failure` controls the recovery path on non-zero exit. See\n    the :data:`OnFailure` type alias for policy semantics.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    name: str\n    cmd: str\n    on_failure: OnFailure = \"fail\"\n    env: dict[str, str] = field(default_factory=dict)\n\n\n# ---------- Workflow ----------\n\n\ndef _default_applies_to(prd: \"PRD\", prds: dict[str, \"PRD\"]) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Default ``applies_to`` predicate — matches nothing.\n\n    Concrete workflows override this in their ``workflow.py`` module.\n    Kept as a module-level function rather than a lambda so mypy and\n    pickling (if ever needed) both behave.\n    \"\"\"\n    return False\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass Workflow:\n    \"\"\"A named recipe for implementing one kind of PRD.\n\n    Authored in ``tools/prd-harness/workflows/<name>/workflow.py`` as a\n    module-level ``workflow = Workflow(...)`` attribute. The loader\n    discovers it, imports the module, and sets :attr:`workflow_dir` to\n    the subdirectory path so AgentTask prompt paths resolve correctly.\n\n    :attr:`priority` orders workflows during assignment: higher numbers\n    win when multiple predicates match. ``default`` has priority 0 and\n    acts as a catchall. Ties are broken alphabetically by name.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    name: str\n    description: str = \"\"\n    applies_to: AppliesToPredicate = field(default=_default_applies_to)\n    priority: int = 0\n    tasks: list[Task] = field(default_factory=list)\n    workflow_dir: Path | None = None\n\n\n# ---------- ExecutionContext ----------\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass ExecutionContext:\n    \"\"\"State threaded through every task during a workflow run.\n\n    Tasks mutate this object in place as the workflow progresses:\n\n    - ``ensure_worktree`` sets :attr:`worktree_path` and :attr:`cwd`\n    - The agent invoke populates :attr:`agent_output` and\n      :attr:`agent_success`\n    - ``create_pr`` sets :attr:`pr_url`\n\n    The runner creates one context at the start of ``run_workflow`` and\n    passes it to each task in order. Tasks read from it (for formatting\n    commit messages, composing prompts, etc.) and write to it (to record\n    side effects for downstream tasks or the CLI to surface).\n\n    :attr:`dry_run` tells builtins, shell tasks, and the agent invoke to\n    log what they WOULD do without actually invoking subprocesses, git,\n    or gh. Drives the ``prd plan`` output.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    prd: \"PRD\"\n    repo_root: Path\n    workflow: Workflow\n    base_ref: str\n    branch_name: str\n    worktree_path: Path | None = None\n    cwd: Path = field(default_factory=Path.cwd)\n    agent_output: str | None = None\n    agent_success: bool = False\n    pr_url: str | None = None\n    run_summary: str | None = None\n    last_invoke_result: \"InvokeResult | None\" = None\n    model: str | None = None\n    invoke_count: int = 0\n    dry_run: bool = True\n    logger: logging.Logger = field(\n        default_factory=lambda: logging.getLogger(\"darkfactory\")\n    )\n    # Advisory process-level lock held by ensure_worktree for the\n    # lifetime of this run. Managed by builtins + runner; tests should\n    # not touch it directly.\n    _worktree_lock: \"FileLock | None\" = field(default=None, repr=False)\n\n    def format_string(self, template: str) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Expand ``{placeholder}`` tokens against context state.\n\n        Supported placeholders:\n\n        - ``{prd_id}`` — the PRD's id (e.g. ``PRD-070``)\n        - ``{prd_title}`` — the PRD's title\n        - ``{prd_slug}`` — the slug portion of the PRD filename\n        - ``{branch}`` — the current branch name\n        - ``{base_ref}`` — the base ref the branch was created from\n        - ``{worktree}`` — the worktree path as a string, or ``\"\"`` if\n          the worktree hasn't been created yet\n\n        Unknown placeholders raise ``KeyError`` (intentionally strict —\n        workflow authors should catch typos early). Contrast with the\n        agent prompt templater in ``templates.py``, which leaves unknown\n        placeholders unchanged to allow incremental template evolution.\n        \"\"\"\n        return template.format(\n            prd_id=self.prd.id,\n            prd_title=self.prd.title,\n            prd_slug=self.prd.slug,\n            branch=self.branch_name,\n            base_ref=self.base_ref,\n            worktree=str(self.worktree_path) if self.worktree_path else \"\",\n        )\n","numLines":272,"startLine":1,"totalLines":272}}}
